>> title: Almond Cookies
>> author: Todd Wilbur

Preheat your oven to 175°C (350°F).

In a medium @bowl{}, whisk together @all-purpose flour{3%cups}, @baking soda{1%tsp}, and @salt{1/2%tsp}.

Grind @blanched almonds{1/2%cup} in a @blender{} or @food processor{} until they reach a fine powder. Stir this almond powder into the flour mixture.

In a separate large @bowl{}, cream together @granulated sugar{1%cup}, @lard{1 1/2%cups} (or @vegetable shortening{1 1/2%cups}), @almond extract{1%tsp}, @egg{1%large}, and @water{1/8%cup} until well combined.

Gradually add the dry flour mixture to the wet ingredients and mix thoroughly until a dough forms.

Roll the dough into 1-inch balls. Place them on an ungreased @cookie sheet{} about 2 inches apart.

Press one of the remaining @blanched almonds{1/2%cup} into the center of each ball, flattening the cookie slightly with your fingers as you do so.

Lightly brush the top of each cookie with @beaten egg{1%large}.

Bake for ~{20%minutes}, or until the edges are lightly browned.
